│ model disagreed\");\n\nReplace with logic akin to:\n- Create CostCtxBest and  │
│ CostCtxLegacy.\n- precomputeCosts for both plans.\n- assertion condition      │
│ becomes:\n  BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width ||\n                           │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(BestPlan, CostCtxBest, OrigLoop) ||\n   │
│ planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(LegacyPlan, CostCtxLegacy,              │
│ OrigLoop)\n\nThis preserves the original invariant intent (disallow silent    │
│ disagreement) while correctly accounting for simplifications in either        │
│ direction.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash stems from an asymmetric verification │
│ assertion that only inspects the BestPlan for simplifications, missing cases  │
│ where the alternative (legacy-selected) plan differs structurally, leading to │
│ benign VF disagreements. Expanding the assertion to examine both plans (with  │
│ separate cost contexts) prevents false positives and avoids the abort. The    │
│ functional behavior (chosen VF for transformation) remains unchanged; only    │
│ the validation logic is corrected to reflect acceptable discrepancies due to  │
│ plan differences.\nExpected effect: Assertion no longer fires for valid plan  │
│ divergences, eliminating the crash for the provided reproducer while          │
│ maintaining robustness of cost model verification.\n"})                       │
